ce:section.ce:para:
To 40ml of 2-methoxymethanol, 4-bromo-N-allyl- naphthalimide (1.58g, 5.0mmol), 2ml of 2-aminomethyl pyridine and 10mg of hydroquinone (as a polymerization inhibitor) were added. Then, the mixture was stirred and refluxed at 127°C under nitrogen atmosphere. The reaction was monitored by thin layer chromatography (TLC) with silica gel plates and a xylene/ethyl acetate (2:1v/v) eluent system. When the reaction was completed, the solvent was removed using a rotary evaporator. The residue was dissolved with 8.0ml of ethanol. The product was precipitated by adding 20.0ml ether and collected by filtration. After being recrystallizated by ethyl acetate, it was dried in vacuum at room temperature. The product was obtained as a yellow solid in 80.5% yield. m.p.: 141–142°C. Elemental Anal. Calcd. (%) for C21H17N3O2: C 73.47, H 4.96, N 12.24; found: C 73.21, H 5.04, N 12.11; FT-IR ν (cm−1): 3435, 3069, 2955, 1701, 1633, 1662, 1589, 1570, 1502, 1425, 1369, 1325, 1232, 1082, 1001, 931,845, 779, 750, 715, 690, 565, 478, 422; 1H NMR (DMSO-d
                           6,500MHz): δ 2.50 (t, 3H, NHCH2); 4.0 (d, 2H, NHCH2
                           ), 4.64–4.65 (d, 2H, NCH2
                           CH=); 5.98-5.90 (m, 1H, NCH2
                           CH

                           =
                           ); 5.19 (d, 1H, =CHa
                           ), 5.12 (d, 1H, =CHb
                           ); 7.23-8.00 (m, 4H, ArH); 8.10-8.22 (d, 2H, ArH); 8.25-8.36 (d, 1H, ArH); 8.55–8.59 (q, 2H, ArH).
